The save_object method is part of a CmdStanFit R6 class. Current signature: save_object(file, ...). The method ensures all CmdStan output is loaded into memory before saving. Key code structure:

r
save_object <- function(file, ...) {
  self$draws()
  try(self$sampler_diagnostics(), silent = TRUE)
  try(self$init(), silent = TRUE)
  try(self$profiles(), silent = TRUE)
  saveRDS(self, file = file, ...)
  invisible(self)
}


The qs2 package provides `qs_save()` and `qs_read()` functions for fast serialization.
